==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Furfurol
<hw>Fur"fu*rol</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>furfur</ets> bran + <ets>ole</ets>um oil.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A colorless oily liquid, <chform>C4H3O.CHO</chform>, of a pleasant
odor, obtained by the distillation of bran, sugar, etc., and regarded as
an aldehyde derivative of furfuran; -- called also
<altname>furfural</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Furfurous</ent>⟦br⟧
